# KeepnetLabs Vue 2 Frontend Development Rules

## 🎯 PROJECT OVERVIEW

The project aims to develop a **KeepnetLabs Human Risk Management** platform for web users.
**Mission:** Transform human risk into human resilience.

Phishing, social‑engineering and user error still trigger the majority of breaches.
The platform reframes this as a human‑risk problem and couples continuous measurement with adaptive controls to shrink that risk over time.
AI‑driven "best‑of‑suite" platform that unifies training, behavioural telemetry and automated controls under one console.

### Core Benefits
- **Quantify human risk:** Individual & org‑level risk scores pull from phishing tests, password hygiene, email behaviour and policy violations
- **Lower breach probability:** Average Phish‑prone % drops from >30% to <5% in 12 months when programmes run continuously
- **Reduce incident‑response effort:** Automates triage & remediation of >85% of user‑reported emails

### Scale & Performance Requirements
- **1,000 organizations** and **500,000 users**
- **95% user engagement**, **99.9% uptime**, **10,000 monthly risk assessments**
- **<1000ms response time** for real-time analytics

---

## 🛠️ TECH STACK

### Core Framework
- **Vue 2.7.8** (Options API only)
- **Vuetify 2.6.9** (Material Design)
- **Vuex 3.4.0** + **Vue Router 3.3.4**
- **Axios 0.27.2** + **Sentry** (Error tracking)

### Key Libraries
- **Forms:** vue-tel-input, v-mask, awesome-phonenumber
- **Charts:** chart.js, vue-chartjs
- **Rich Text:** GrapesJS + plugins
- **Security:** sanitize-html
- **Testing:** jest, @vue/test-utils

